<TITLE> BNP whip gets bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, Apr 11 (bdnews24.com)  Opposition chief whip and BNP publicity secretary Zainul Abdin Farroque on Sunday secured bail in a criminal case filed in Sylhet. Sylhet Chief Judicial Magistrate Md Amiruddin granted the BNP leader's bail upon his petition after he appeared before the court on Sunday. Safiul Alam Chowdhury Nadel, former president of Sylhet district Bangladesh Chhatra League and also a former educational affairs secretary of the metropolitan Awami League, filed the case against the BNP leader on Mar 16 on charges of 'intentionally defaming' prime minister Sheikh Hasina's son Sajeeb Ahmed Wazed. Plaintiff's lawyer advocate Araz Ali said the court had taken the case into cognisance on Mar 16 and had ordered Farroque to appear on Apr 15. Farroque appeared before the court four days prior to the court's fixed date. bdne
